Email.Description: Name of the attribute within the SAML assert to use as the users email in Grafana.

Groups.Description: Name of the attribute within the SAML assert to use as the users groups in Grafana.

Login.Description: Name of the attribute within the SAML assert to use as the users login handle in Grafana.

Name.Description: Name of the attribute within the SAML assert to use as the users name in Grafana.

Org.Description: Name of the attribute within the SAML assert to use as the users organizations in Grafana.

Role.Description: Name of the attribute within the SAML assert to use as the users roles in Grafana.

Url.Description: URL that vends the IdPs metadata.

Xml.Description: XML blob of the IdPs metadata.

Admin.Description: List of SAML roles which will be mapped into the Grafana Admin role.

Editor.Description: List of SAML roles which will be mapped into the Grafana Editor role.

AllowedOrganizations.Description: List of SAML organizations allowed to access Grafana.

LoginValidityDuration.Description: The maximum lifetime an authenticated user can be logged in (in minutes) before being required to re-authenticate.

SecurityGroupIds.Description: The list of Amazon EC2 security group IDs attached to the Amazon VPC for your Grafana workspace to connect.

SubnetIds.Description: The list of Amazon EC2 subnet IDs created in the Amazon VPC for your Grafana workspace to connect.

AuthenticationProviders.Description: List of authentication providers to enable.

ClientToken.Description: A unique, case-sensitive, user-provided identifier to ensure the idempotency of the request.

CreationTimestamp.Description: Timestamp when the workspace was created.

DataSources.Description: List of data sources on the service managed IAM role.

GrafanaVersion.Description: Version of Grafana the workspace is currently using.

Id.Description: The id that uniquely identifies a Grafana workspace.

ModificationTimestamp.Description: Timestamp when the workspace was last modified

Name.Description: The user friendly name of a workspace.

NotificationDestinations.Description: List of notification destinations on the customers service managed IAM role that the Grafana workspace can query.

OrganizationRoleName.Description: The name of an IAM role that already exists to use with AWS Organizations to access AWS data sources and notification channels in other accounts in an organization.

OrganizationalUnits.Description: List of Organizational Units containing AWS accounts the Grafana workspace can pull data from.

RoleArn.Description: IAM Role that will be used to grant the Grafana workspace access to a customers AWS resources.

SsoClientId.Description: The client ID of the AWS SSO Managed Application.

StackSetName.Description: The name of the AWS CloudFormation stack set to use to generate IAM roles to be used for this workspace.
